Commented on #176 Wrong `could not execute: tasty-discover`

Happen to know the proper response. Back in the day (but most probably before this report), I put info how to properly bootstrap tasty-discover. Notice build-tool-depends: in: https://github.com/haskell-works/tasty-discover#configure-cabal-or-hpack-test-suite
tasty-discover is not really a library dependency, it is a testing tool executable. tasty-discover should not be build-depends: it is build-tool-depends:
When tool is in .cabal description build-tool-depends: - Cabal automatically installs & uses the executable. BTW cabal2nix also follows, respects & supports build-tool-depends:. Please, check that it solves the configuration.
